Which file contains information about the filesystems to mount, their partitions, and theoptions that should be used to mount them?
A)  /etc/filesystems
B)  /etc/mounts
C)  /etc/fstab
D)  systemd.mount
C
C. The /etc/fstab file is used to store information about the filesystems to mount withinthe system. The systemd.mount option refers to the configuration files used by systemdrelated to filesystems.
